               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-986" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-986" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-986" type="surname" value="BAKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-986" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE BAKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cheesemonger, and live in King David-lane, Shadwell. About half-past five o'clock in the afternoon, on the 29th of Sept., I saw the prisoner with a boy in front of my shop—I turned to go into the back parlour—I was not gone a minute when I was called by a neighbour, and missed a piece of bacon from my window—I went out, and saw the pri<lb></lb>soner running about twenty-five yards off—I saw him throw the bacon down—a person picked it up, and gave it to me—this is it—here is where put the ticket on it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-987" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-987" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-987" type="surname" value="CHADLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-987" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES CHADLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in King David-lane—I saw the prisoner and a boy sitting on the railings nearly opposite Mr. Baker's shop—the boy went and took the bacon, and went to the corner—the prisoner walked up and took the bacon from him—he was round the corner—I ran after the boy, but did not catch him.</p>
               <p>
